.TH "nilfs_ioctl_set_alloc_range" 9 "nilfs_ioctl_set_alloc_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_ioctl_set_alloc_range \- limit range of segments to be allocated
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_ioctl_set_alloc_range
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "void __user *argp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode object
.IP "argp" 12
pointer on argument from userspace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Decription: \fBnilfs_ioctl_set_alloc_range\fP function defines lower limit
of segments in bytes and upper limit of segments in bytes.
The NILFS_IOCTL_SET_ALLOC_RANGE is used by nilfs_resize utility.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned or error code, otherwise.
